726361f-c.title: Queens: Colonial Avenue - 62nd Drive
726361f-c.text:
Colonial Ave., (right side of house not shown) west side,
orth of 62nd Drive. If locating in 1922, it would be on Mill Creek
nd Old Mill Road. At the street line of the S.W. corner of
orace Hiarding Boulevard and Colonial Avenue is the site of this
ouse which was rased in Sept 193O to make way for the Horace
arding Boulevard. Judge Robert Coe erected the house in 1655.
he following year he moved to Jamaica and Captain John Coe be-
ame the owner of the farmhouse and the Mill property which was
n the west side of the Creek. In 1698 Judge John Coe, 2nd son
f Captain John Coe was the owner. This family retained possession
or almost a century when about 1810 David Titus became the owner.
e in turn sold to Daniel Rapelye son of Major Rapelye who was
till the o.mer in 1852. Mrs. Nenny was an occupant in 1922.
ugene L. Armbruster states that the Lott farily also owned this
rop-rty. The mill was destroyed by fire in 1875. L. J. Wood,
. Felton, or R. v. Hitchcock was the owner in 1873. The present
tructure was erected about 1750 on the site of the old house.
ne Van Rieper however states it to be the original Coe house.
ne Earll was the owner of this property in 188O. Thomas G. Smith
f the Shady Lake farm was the owner in 1910. According to
igures inscribed on a stone in the building, the house was said
n 1925 to be 216 years old. View No. 3 shows the house at the
ight background. Mill Creek is in the foreground.
Jan. 1926
Views 1, 2 and 3.
Vgene L. Armbruster Collection
AY BE REPRODUCED.

726359f-d.title: Queens: Colonial Avenue - N. of 62nd Drive.
726359f-d.text:
Colonial Ave., east side, north of 62nd Drive. In the fore-
ground of view No. 1 is 62nd Drive at left where it makes a turn.
It was then known (1922) as North Hempstead Plank Drive. The houses
seen in the foreground belong to De La Corte who conducts an Inn.
here. In the background is the Flushing ash dump. The path at the
oright foreground became a part of 110th Street.
March 1925

View 3:4:1922
